    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-02T07:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-02T07:35:00-05:00" n="654"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No 861.00/2879</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-02T16:00:00+03:25">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 3, 3.23 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Department’s circular of September 20, 6 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    states he will send appropriate instructions to Persian Chargé d’Affaires in
                    Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJK1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
